A queue implementation is linearizable wrt. queue semantics if
whenever two element are enqueued sequentially the younger element
is not removed before the older element.
The Timestamped Queue is linearizable wrt. queue semantics.
For queues a local correctness condition translates into global correctness.
For stacks recursive dependencies are possible.
No global linearization order is possible.
